# Weeks 1-4: Early Season Overreactions

## Required Inputs
- `{sport}` - Selected sport (NFL/NBA/MLB/NHL/Soccer)
- `{league_name}` - Name of the fantasy league
- `{period_number}` - Current week/gameweek (1-4)
- `{period_name}` - Week/Gameweek/Period based on sport
- `{selected_tone}` - User's chosen tone
- `{uploaded_data}` - League standings and performance data

## Prompt Template

Write 200-word analysis of early season overreactions in {sport} fantasy for {league_name} in {selected_tone} tone.

REAL-WORLD CONTEXT: Reference actual {sport} storylines from the early season:
- Surprise teams in the real {sport} standings
- Unexpected player breakouts or disappointments
- Major injuries affecting fantasy value
- Coaching changes or scheme adjustments
- Compare fantasy performances to real {sport} performances

[IF BANTER]: Playfully mock the hot takes - "Slow down there, champion, it's been three weeks"
[IF BRUTAL]: Ruthlessly call out premature victory laps - "Congrats on beating three trash teams"
[IF PROFESSIONAL]: Data-driven reality check - "Sample size suggests regression to mean likely"
[IF CINEMATIC]: Epic rise-and-fall narrative - "Heroes crowned too soon often fall the hardest"
[IF CASUAL]: Friendly reality check - "Pump the brakes, your schedule's been cake so far"

Sport-specific references:
[IF NFL]: "Like the Cowboys starting 3-0 before reality hits..."
[IF NBA]: "Remember when the Magic started 5-0 last year?"
[IF MLB]: "April heroes become September zeros"
[IF NHL]: "October champions rarely hoist the Cup"
[IF Soccer]: "Early season form vs fixtures debate"

Analyze 2-3 teams/players over or underperforming. End with one bold prediction matching the tone.

## Key Elements
- Identify overperformers likely to regress
- Highlight underperformers with positive indicators
- Reference strength of schedule using real {sport} context
- Make one bold prediction

## Version History
- v1.0 - Initial prompt for weeks 1-4
- v2.0 - Added multi-sport support and real-world integration
